Subject: Query on FSAA Job requiring 'Create Schema Job' to be run.
Description:
We're testing the FSAA scan since the upgrade to v11.6 and we're getting errors that ask for the 'Create Schema Job' to be run. The job is disabled and we want to verify if there would be any impact to running the job, as this is our production environment.

Any help or guidance that could be provided via email or call would be greatly appreciated. Thank you.
Solution_Comment__c:
All of that aside: this is caused by the update to 11.6, and you just need to run the job mentioned on every NEA server we've upgraded. Here's the article for you to do that: https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Solutions/FileSystem/Collection/0-Create_Schema.htm

FileSystem > 0.Collection > 0-Create Schema > Configure node and select Analysis

Run the 1. Create Tables – Creates all tables prefaced with SA_FSAA_ Job, and the error message should go away.
